  "subject": "Correct KUD addons installation issues",
  "commit_message": "Correct KUD addons installation issues\n\nOvn-kubernetes addon was installing helm, that conflicted with\none installed by kubespray. Istio addon attempted to use too old\nversion of ansible-galaxy role, that didn't support demanded\ngo version. Both of these issues have been corrected in this commit.\n\nIssue-ID: MULTICLOUD-690\n\nSigned-off-by: Konrad Bańka <k.banka@samsung.com>\nChange-Id: Id8c5c7c65d4f6f47ed42bedc7de44b1d7d2f17cc\n",
